# Card Layout Rules

All cards in mockup pages follow consistent layout patterns.

## Food Item Cards (`.item-card`)

Structure: **graphic**, **name**, **tag** (optional).

- Cards use `display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center` with a `min-height`
- The graphic (`.sa`) gets `margin-top: auto` to push it **down** away from the top border
- The food name (`.item-name`) gets a fixed `margin-top` (e.g. `6px`) for consistent spacing
- Name and tag sit at the **bottom**, aligned across all cards regardless of graphic height

## Entity Cards (`.entity-card`)

Structure: **sprite-area** (64x64), **name**, **behavior**, **theme** (italic).

- Cards use a **fixed height** (`height: 170px`), `flex-direction: column`, `align-items: center`, `gap: 6px`
- The sprite area (`.sprite-area`, 64x64px) is centered at the top with `margin-bottom: 8px` for a paragraph-sized gap before text
- The theme line (`.entity-theme`, italic) gets `margin-top: auto` to **pin it to the bottom** of the card, ensuring consistent positioning regardless of behavior text length
- All text between sprite and theme flows naturally with the flex gap

```css
.entity-card { height: 170px; gap: 6px; }
.sprite-area { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.entity-theme { margin-top: auto; }
```

## Key Principle

Sprites/graphics are top-anchored with consistent spacing to text below. The bottom-most label is always pinned to the card bottom via `margin-top: auto`. Empty space distributes between the flowing text and the pinned bottom label — never between the sprite and its name.
